Job description

The Company

MDA National supports more than 54,000 Members and insured by providing the best possible support, care and protection so they can do their best for patients. Whether the member is a student, or a specialist with decades of experience, our insurance does more than simply cover our members. It means we're there for them with advice and expertise whenever they need it.


MDA National takes pride in a workplace culture focused on people, core values and collaborative relationships. While we function as a national organisation, with offices in all six Australian states and “virtual” support in ACT and NT, our unified ‘one office culture’ remains a constant focus. We aim to attract the right people, based on professional skills and personal attributes, to ensure they are the ‘best fit’ for the organisation.


The Role \xa0

Reporting directly to the Technical Lead, the role will include (but not be limited to) the following:

  • Providing .NET programming support to the Information, Communications and Technology (ICT) Department
  • Providing SharePoint, Pivotal CRM and Sitecore development and operational support
  • Designing programs and components to meet business requirements
  • Working with and provide technical input and analysis to the ICT Team
  • Assisting with developing components for online systems and administration
  • Liaising with Third Party Vendors to meet business requirements
  • Performing system integration, change management and testing tasks
  • Working with Service Desk to meet agreed SLA’s


Skills & Experience \xa0 \xa0

The ideal candidate will have the following:

  • A strong .NET programming background, preferably C# based

  • A solid understanding of n-tier applications and distributed programming

  • A strong understanding of SQL Server and back-end programming

  • A solid understanding of XML and related technologies (SOAP, REST, HTTP etc) and related programming languages (XSLT, XPATH, Linq2Xml etc).

  • A strong understanding of front end website programming (e.g. ASP.NET, MVC)

  • A degree or tertiary qualification in Information Technology or Computer Science and/or;

\xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 position relevant vendor or industry recognised qualifications

  • ITIL Foundation qualification


What's on Offer

  • Fantastic opportunity to join a well-established organisation where you are a person, not a number

  • Outstanding team culture where staff produce excellent results

  • Access to personalised development plans

  • Endless free fruit, tea, coffee and snacks

  • Health & wellbeing benefits including a 24/7 EAP program and healthcare discounts

  • Income protection insurance

Job description

The Role:

Machine learning is a crucial part of what we do at black. We like developing things from scratch and performing several experiments rapidly.
As a Machine Learning Engineer at black, you must have a fundamental understanding of machine learning and embedded systems.
We seek candidates with a passion for high performance computing, robotics and complex analysis, who wish to become global authorities in the field of AI and take pride in implementing cutting-edge research.
You will be working closely with our Research team and Software Developers to co-develop machine learning solutions for a variety of different tasks and projects.
This is a full time position in our Melbourne office.

Requirements:
- Very proficient in Python/Bash/C/C++ programming
- MSc graduate with a background in mathematics or computer science
- An academic background OR equivalent practical experience in implementing:
i. Modern deep learning (CNNs, RNNs, LSTMs, GANs)
ii. Traditional methods of deep learning (Random Decision Forests, Gradient Boosting, SVM, HOG)
- Strong knowledge of recently developed machine learning approaches. You carefully read the relevant papers and can confidently explain how most modern deep learning networks function down to first principles
- 2+ years experience using Unix variant OS
- Experience with Tensorflow, Darknet, TensorRT
- Decent portfolio of prior ML projects
- Able to work autonomously and be self-driven

We understand, however, that academic experience is not always indicative of ability. So if you believe that you would be suitable for this role due to having a large amount of hands on, practical experience, please don’t hesitate to apply.
